programme.title: Ken Burns' Baseball
programme.desc: Seventh inning (1950-60). "The Shot Heard 'Round the World," Bobby Thomson's pennant-winning home run in 1950; Abbott and Costello's "Who's on First"; Casey Stengel, Yogi Berra, Mickey Mantle and Willie Mays; the Dodgers and Giants move to California. John Chancellor narrates. (cc)

programme.title: Ken Burns' Baseball
programme.desc: Eighth inning (1960-70). Bill Mazeroski's 1960 Series-winning home run; Roger Maris's 61 homers in '61; Bob Gibson, Carl Yastrzemski, Stan Musial and Sandy Koufax; football's growing popularity; Marvin Miller and the players' union; Curt Flood's stand against the reserve clause. John Chancellor narrates. (cc)

programme.title: Ken Burns' Baseball
programme.desc: Ninth inning (1970-1993). Game 6 of the '75 Reds-Red Sox World Series; free agency and collusion; the death of Jackie Robinson; Hank Aaron breaks the career HR mark; the "Big Red Machine"; owners Charles Finley and George Steinbrenner; the "curse" of the Red Sox; Roberto Clemente, Pete Rose, Reggie Jackson and Nolan Ryan. John Chancellor narrates. (cc)

programme.title: Ken Burns' Baseball
programme.desc: Part 1 of 2. The follow-up to Ken Burns' 1994 series picks up with the crippling '94 strike; the influx of international players; Cal Ripken's consecutive-games streak; and the thrilling 1998 home-run race between Mark McGwire and Sammy Sosa. (cc)

programme.title: Ken Burns' Baseball
programme.desc: The documentary concludes with a look at Japan's first big MLB star, Ichiro Suzuki; the comfort provided by the game after the 9/11 attacks; revelations about performance-enhancing drugs; Boston's rivalry with the Yankees and 2004 World Series victory; and dominating pitchers like Pedro Martinez. (cc)

programme.title: Classic World Series Film: 2011: Cardinals vs. Rangers
programme.desc: From 2011: St. Louis vs. Texas. Unheralded Cardinals 3B David Freese hit his way to MVP of a seven-game drama that sent manager Tony La Russa to retirement on top, while the Rangers and manager Ron Washington swallowed a second-straight Series defeat. (cc)

programme.title: Classic World Series Film: 2012: Giants vs. Tigers
programme.desc: From 2012: San Francisco vs. Detroit. The Giants swept their way to a second championship in three years, holding Detroit to six runs in four games. MVP Pablo Sandoval and closer Sergio Romo were standouts. (cc)

programme.title: Classic World Series Film: 2013: Cardinals vs. Red Sox
programme.desc: From 2013: St. Louis vs. Boston. The Red Sox captured their third championship in 10 years after overcoming St. Louis in six games. David Ortiz, Jon Lester, Koji Uehara and Matt Holliday were among the standout performers. (cc)

programme.title: Classic World Series Film: 2014: Giants vs. Royals
programme.desc: From 2014: San Francisco vs. Kansas City. A pair of wild-card teams waged a seven-game Fall Classic, with MVP Madison Bumgarner carrying the Giants to their third title in five years. The Royals were 8-0 to start their first postseason since 1985. (cc)

programme.title: Classic World Series Film: 2015: Royals vs. Mets
programme.desc: From 2015: Kansas City vs. New York Mets. In their second-straight World Series, Ned Yost's Royals ended a 30-year title drought by coming back in all four of their wins, using baserunning, defense and an airtight bullpen. Salvador Perez was named MVP. (cc)
